AGI -&nbsp;A distance of forty-five years from the murder of the President of the Region Sicily, born the School of Political Formation "
Piersanti Mattarella>”.&nbsp;The School aims to train new generations on the political-institutional level, in the wake of the example of Piersanti Mattarella and the values of which he was an authentic interpreter and bearer.
&nbsp;
The complexity of the modern world, geopolitical tensions, economic and social upheaval, technological transformations, climate change, mass migration, the constant increase in astensionism require greater commitment.<br> &nbsp;
Participation in public and political life is a duty, as President Piersanti Mattarella wrote, deriving from the consideration that the social order contributes to the development and enrichment of the person.&nbsp;<br> In this perspective, training is a necessary and indispensable premise.<br> &nbsp;
The School is inspired by the values of the Constitution, the Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union, the Declaration of Human Rights, Popularism and democratic Catholicism. And he's apartite. It also aims to help seek historical truth, as well as procedural, of the never solved murder of President Piersanti Mattarella, which took place on 6 January 1980.&nbsp;<br> &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Called to assume the role of president, and to coordinate it, is Dr. Paolo Borrometi>, journalist for years engaged in the tale and in the denunciation of the mafias, as well as in the respect and protection of article 21 of the Constitution. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
In the board of directors, among others, are the attendance of the university teacher Antonella Tartaglia Polcini, Dr Jacopo Grasso and Dr Gabriele Uva. The School is enriched by personalities carrying highly qualified experiences that will form the scientific committee. Among these, the former President of the Court of Cassation, Antonio Valitutti, the President of the Association “I Popolari” Pierluigi Castagnetti, the former Minister and already President of the Antimafia commission, Rosy Bindi, the councilman of the National Authority Anticorruzione, Consuelo Del Balzo, the President of the committee “DC80” and former minister, Ortensio Zecchino
&nbsp;
The training will be aimed at young people aged between 18 and 35, from all over Italy. Through scholarships, the School will cover the expenses of registration, accommodation and transport of those who are deprived of means.
&nbsp;
The first appointment of the School will be held on the weekend 23-24-25 May in Rome, on the occasion of the 90th birthday of President Piersanti Mattarella. The second, once again in the Capital, on the weekend 21-22-23 November. All information on how to participate and register is available on www.sfppiersantimattarella.it.&nbsp;

